SWEDEN. 3 Riksdaler, ND (1587). Stockholm Mint. Johan III. NGC AU-53. Dav-LS570; SM-18(18); 
Delzanno-4: not in Hagander (attributes the coinage to the Vadstena Mint); Bruun auction-cf. 508; 
Bruun-11642. Weight: 87.26 gms. Mintmaster: Gillis (Julius) Coyet the elder. While Double and Single Talers 
of this impressive type frequently appear in public auctions, the higher denominations such as this 3 Riksdaler 
are VERY RARE. The elusiveness of the 4 and 3 Riksdalers is underscored by the fact that only one example 
